.TH F00-ECHO 1 "2026" "f00 0.15.5" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
f00\-echo \- display a line of text (f00tils)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B f00\-echo
[\fISHORT\-OPTION\fR]... [\fISTRING\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Echo the STRING(s) to standard output. Pure assembly multicall. MIT.
.PP
Default is modern mode.
.B \-\-core
selects strict GNU echo\-compatible behavior.
.SH COREUTILS FLAGS
.TP
\fB\-n\fR
do not output the trailing newline
.TP
\fB\-e\fR
enable interpretation of backslash escapes
.TP
\fB\-E\fR
disable interpretation of backslash escapes (default)
.PP
See
.B f00\-echo \-\-help
for the full flag list.
.SH MODERN FLAGS
.TP
\fB\-\-core\fR
strict coreutils\-compatible mode
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR / \fB\-\-version\fR
suite meta options
.SH AUTHOR
f00 contributors. License MIT.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR echo (1),
.BR f00\-printf (1),
.BR f00 (1)
.PP
https://f00.sh
